ACTION:
Measure the voltage at the output terminals of the control relay, with the lamp module connected (i.e., under load) and the relay closed. Also verify the current being supplied at this point. This tests for supply voltage collapse or excessive series resistance when current is drawn, distinguishing between a voltage supply problem under load versus a circuit interruption.
